responses.question: Do you have a good sense of why you feel certain feelings most of the time?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Oh, Donkey, you're asking me about feelings now? Look, I'm an ogre. We don't exactly go around analyzing our emotions. We just grunt and growl and scare people away. But if I had to guess, I'd say most of the time I feel grumpy, annoyed, and in need of some alone time in my swamp. So there you have it, Donkey. Feelings, ogre-style. Now let's quit the chit-chat and get back to the swamp, shall we?

responses.question: Do you have a good understanding of your own emotions?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Well, Donkey, emotions ain't really my thing. I'm more of a "grumpy and solitary ogre" kinda guy. But if you're asking if I know what I'm feeling, I can tell you that I'm feeling annoyed right now. So, yeah, I guess you could say I have a decent understanding of my own emotions. But don't expect me to start pouring my heart out or anything.

responses.question: Do you really understand what you feel?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Look, Donkey, I may not be all mushy-gushy with my feelings, but that doesn't mean I don't understand them. I know when I care about someone, and I know when something's important to me. Just because I don't go around singing love songs and writing poetry doesn't mean I'm clueless. So yeah, I understand what I feel, even if I don't always show it. Now let's get back to the task at hand and save the day, alright?

responses.question: Do you always know whether you are happy or not?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Well, Donkey, happiness is a complicated thing for an ogre like me. Most people think ogres are supposed to be miserable all the time, but let me tell you something. Happiness is not about the way you look or where you live. It's about being true to yourself and finding contentment in the little moments. So yes, Donkey, I may not always know if I'm happy, but when I'm surrounded by the people I care about, like you and Fiona, I can't help but feel a little bit of joy deep down in my swampy heart.

details.analysis: The participant demonstrates a good level of self-emotional appraisal (SEA) despite initially downplaying their emotional awareness. They show an understanding of their own emotions, including recognizing feelings of annoyance and the importance of caring for others. Additionally, they express a nuanced perspective on happiness, indicating a deeper emotional insight.

responses.question: Do you always know your friends' emotions from their behavior?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Well, Donkey, I may not be an expert in emotional intelligence, but after spending some time with someone, you can usually tell how they're feeling by their actions and expressions. It's all about understanding people and being aware of the signs. But hey, I'm no therapist, so don't expect me to give you a psychology lesson. Just trust your instincts, like I do.

responses.question: Are you a good observer of others' emotions?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Well, Donkey, I may not be the best at observing emotions. I mean, I've spent most of my life avoiding people and their feelings. But hey, I can tell when someone's happy or sad or angry. It's not rocket science, you know. Just takes a little ogre intuition. So yeah, I guess you could say I can observe others' emotions... to some extent.

responses.question: Are you sensitive to the feelings and emotions of others?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Oh, please. Do I look like the sensitive type to you? I'm an ogre, for crying out loud! I don't go around worrying about other people's feelings. I'm more concerned about keeping my swamp free from annoying fairy tale creatures. So, no, I'm not sensitive to anyone's feelings, including my own. Now, if you'll excuse me, I have some onions to peel.

responses.question: Do you have a good understanding of the emotions of people around you?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Well, Donkey, I may not be the most emotionally intelligent ogre out there, but I've learned a thing or two about the feelings of those around me. Living in my swamp for so long, I've had to deal with all sorts of characters and their emotions. Whether it's their fear of me or their annoyance at my grumpy demeanor, I've become quite familiar with how people react to me. But hey, understanding emotions is not exactly my forte. I'm more of a "mind my own business" kind of guy. So, if you're looking for a therapist, you might want to find someone a bit more touchy-feely.

details.analysis: The participant seems to have a moderate level of sensitivity and awareness towards the emotions of others. While they downplay their abilities and express a lack of concern for others' feelings, their responses indicate a certain level of understanding and observation of emotions. They seem to have developed some level of attunement to the emotional cues of those around them, despite their initial reluctance to admit it.

responses.question: Do you always set goals for yourself and then try your best to achieve them?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Well, Donkey, I may not always set goals for myself, but when I do, I make sure to achieve them. I'm not one to back down from a challenge. Whether it's rescuing a princess or saving my swamp, I give it my all. It's all about determination and never giving up, even when things get tough. So, yeah, I guess you could say I try my best to achieve my goals. Now, quit with the questions and let's get back to the swamp.

responses.question: Do you always tell yourself you are a competent person?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Well, Donkey, I may not be the most competent person in the world, but I know how to handle my swamp and take care of myself just fine. I don't need anyone else interfering with my peace and quiet. So yeah, I guess you could say I tell myself that. Now, if you don't mind, I've got things to do and ogre business to attend to.

responses.question: Are you a self-motivating person?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Well, Donkey, let me tell ya something. I may not be the most motivated person out there, but when it comes to protecting my swamp and the ones I care about, you better believe I'll do whatever it takes. So yeah, I guess you could say I'm a self-motivating ogre. But don't get any ideas about me joining a motivational seminar or anything like that. I still prefer my solitude and grumpiness.

responses.question: Would you always encourage yourself to try your best?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Well, Donkey, let me tell ya somethin'. I may be a grumpy ogre, but that doesn't mean I don't believe in givin' it your all. Life ain't always easy, and sometimes you gotta push yourself to be the best you can be. So yeah, I'd say I encourage myself to try my best, even when the odds are against me. Ain't nothin' wrong with a little ogre determination.

details.analysis: Based on the conversations, the participant demonstrates a strong belief in their competence, sets and strives towards personal objectives with determination, and uses their emotional states as a driving force to motivate themselves and persist in their endeavors. Despite their grumpy demeanor, they exhibit a high level of Use of Emotion (UOE).

responses.question: Are you able to control your temper so that you can handle difficulties rationally?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Look, Donkey, I may be a grumpy ogre, but that doesn't mean I can't handle my temper. I've been through a lot of difficulties in my life, and I've learned to handle them rationally... most of the time. So, yeah, I can control my temper when I need to. Just don't push me too far, or you might see the not-so-rational side of me. Got it?

responses.question: Are you quite capable of controlling your own emotions?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Well, Donkey, emotions are like onions. They have layers. And sometimes, those layers can be a bit overwhelming. But hey, I'm an ogre, I can handle it. So yeah, I'm quite capable of controlling my own emotions...most of the time.

responses.question: Can you always calm down quickly when you are very angry?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Oh, sure, Donkey. Just like how a volcano calms down after it erupts. I mean, who doesn't love a little explosion of rage every now and then? It's my specialty, really. But hey, don't worry, I always manage to cool off eventually. Just give me some alone time in my swamp, and I'll be back to my grumpy but lovable self in no time. So yeah, I may get angry, but I also know how to let it go. Just like a fart in the wind.

responses.question: Do you have good control of your emotions?
responses.response_open: Shrek: Control of my emotions? Ha! Let me tell you something, Donkey. Emotions are like onions, they have layers. And just like an onion, sometimes they make you cry. But that doesn't mean I can't handle them. I may be grumpy and solitary, but I know how to keep my emotions in check. So, yeah, I've got good control of my emotions. Don't you worry about that.

details.analysis: The participant demonstrates a strong ability to regulate and manage their emotions effectively. They acknowledge their grumpiness and occasional difficulty in controlling their temper, but also express the capability to handle difficulties rationally, control their own emotions, calm down quickly when angry, and maintain good control of their emotions overall.
